<TITLE> Learner driver kills morning walker on DU campus </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 22 (bdnews24.com)A learner driver ran over and killed a morning walker on Dhaka University campus on Monday, police and witnesses said. Witnesses said a professor's wife, Anima Rani Shaha, was run over as the driver, 22-year old 'Fahim', lost control of his vehicle and drove onto the footpath. Shahbagh police chief Rezaul Karim said Anima, wife of Parimal Kumar Shaha of DU's Institute of Education Research, was taken to Dhaka Medical College Hospital at around 7am. She was pronounced dead at the hospital, he said. bd
